{"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GThreadPool"},{"type":"text","text":" struct represents a thread pool."}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"sections":[],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Initializers","generated":true,"title":"Initializers","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/init(_:)-1r3ft","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/init(_:)-3sb8k","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/init(_:)-5qqyk","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/init(_:)-949on","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/init(_:)-xcct","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/init(cPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/init(gconstpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/init(gpointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/init(opaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/init(raw:)-14ipo","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/init(raw:)-49ior","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/init(retaining:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/init(retainingCPointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/init(retainingOpaquePointer:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/init(retainingRaw:)-2gqbl","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/init(retainingRaw:)-53ai8"]},{"anchor":"Instance-Properties","title":"Instance Properties","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/ptr"]},{"generated":true,"title":"Type Methods","anchor":"Type-Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/new(full:userData:itemFreeFunc:maxThreads:exclusive:)"]},{"title":"Default Implementations","generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool\/ThreadPoolProtocol-Implementations"],"anchor":"Default-Implementations"}],"relationshipsSections":[{"type":"conformsTo","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol"],"title":"Conforms To","kind":"relationships"}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ThreadPool","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ThreadPool"}],"role":"symbol","title":"ThreadPool","roleHeading":"Class","symbolKind":"class","externalID":"s:4GLib10ThreadPoolC"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"ThreadPool"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"overview","type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A thread pool is useful when you wish to asynchronously fork out the execution of work"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and continue working in your own thread. If that will happen often, the overhead of starting","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and destroying a thread each time might be too high. In such cases reusing already started","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"threads seems like a good idea. And it indeed is, but implementing this can be tedious"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and error-prone.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Therefore GLib provides thread pools for your convenience. An added advantage is, that the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"threads can be shared between the different subsystems of your program, when they are using GLib."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a new thread pool, you use [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.new"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It is destroyed by [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.free","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you want to execute a certain task within a thread pool, use [method"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.push","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To get the current number of running threads you call [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_num_threads"},{"type":"text","text":"]."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"To get the number of still unprocessed tasks you call [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.unprocessed"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"To control the maximum number of threads for a thread pool, you use","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_max_threads"},{"type":"text","text":"]. and [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.set_max_threads"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Finally you can control the number of unused threads, that are kept alive by GLib for future use.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"The current number can be fetched with [func","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_num_unused_threads"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The maximum number can be controlled by [func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.get_max_unused_threads"},{"text":"] and","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.ThreadPool.set_max_unused_threads"},{"type":"text","text":"]. All currently unused threads"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"can be stopped by calling [func"},{"code":"GLib.ThreadPool.stop_unused_threads","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool"},{"text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GThreadPool"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolProtocol","type":"reference"},{"text":" conformance.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" as a strong reference or owner of a "},{"code":"GThreadPool","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" instance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPoolRef","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" (instead of "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/ThreadPool","isActive":true},{"text":") for a lightweight Swift reference to an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GThreadPool"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}]}],"style":"note","name":"Note"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/threadpool"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/ThreadPool/init(raw:)-14ipo":{"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"init"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"raw"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SV","text":"UnsafeRawPointer"},{"text":")","kind":"te